content.raw:
Thanks for the instructions!

When I check out that branch and use all the latest `gz11`/`default` branches and then run that command, I get the following error message in the terminal output:

```
[libprotobuf ERROR google/protobuf/text_format.cc:298] Error parsing text-format ignition.msgs.EntityFactory: 1:667: Message type "ignition.msgs.EntityFactory" has no field named "name".
data: true
```

and nothing seems to spawn. The `ign-gazebo` terminal prints:

```
[Err] [UserCommands.cc:244] model field not yet supported.
```

If I run the same command but remove the `name` field, I don't get the `libprotobuf` error, but I still get the `ign-gazebo` error.

Am I maybe using the wrong combination of branches?

It's not critical for this issue though, since I think [this test](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-physics/pull-requests/65/use-ode-for-collision-detection-instead-of/diff#comment-90890092) is good enough verification.
